    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "it's just so frustrating to feel like i'm fighting an uphill battle. it almost feels like these little hidden costs are intentionally designed to keep you stuck in debt. is there anything else besides fees that makes the debt feel so much more aggressive or \"hidden\" than the actual principal amount?",
