      "content": "The primary reason payments feel aggressive is the combination of your fixed payment amount being allocated almost entirely to interest while fees reduce the already small amount of principal payment each month. Additionally, prepayment penalties on some private loans can discourage you from paying off the balance early to stop the interest clock. Ultimately, whatever \"hidden\" method you are encountering, the most effective solution is making every possible extra payment toward the principal balance directly. This reduces the interest calculated on the next month, accelerating the payoff regardless of other structural factors.",
